[I] KDE Frameworks integration module for idle time detection

[T] KIdleTime is a singleton reporting information on idle time. It is useful
[T] not only for finding out about the current idle time of the PC, but also
[T] for getting notified upon idle time events, such as custom timeouts, or
[T] user activity.

[U] https://www.kde.org

[A] The KDE-Team
